<h1>CloudWalk's CLI - Set up</h1>

<p class="more-info"><%= I18n.t("general.updated_at", :date => "16/09/2014") %></p>

<p>The first thing that you need to do is to install our CLI tool, using the following:</p>

<ul id="index-view-tab" class="nav nav-tabs">
  <li class="active"><a href="#index-tab1">OSX and Linux</a></li>
  <li><a href="#index-tab2">Windows</a></li>
</ul>

<div class="tab-content">
<div class="tab-pane active" id="index-tab1">
<pre><code>$ wget -qO- https://cli.cloudwalk.io/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="tab-pane" id="index-tab2">
  <a href="https://cli.cloudwalk.io/windows.exe" id="file-request" class="btn btn-success">Download</a>
</div>

<p>
Once installed, you can use <code>cloudwalk</code> from your
command line interface, in case you don't have yet a CloudWalk
account, let's create one using the following:
</p>

<code>
  cloudwalk signup
</code>

<p>
  It will ask your basic information to proceed, after that you'll
  need to login, this way:
</p>

<code>
  cloudwalk login
</code>

<p>
Great! Now you're ready to create your new application.
</p>

